-- Saudi’s Marafiq Signs Desalination Plant Agreement, Aswat Says
-- B y   D o n n a   A b u - N a s r
-- 2012-09-27T10:45:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-27/saudi-s-marafiq-signs-desalination-plant-agreement-aswat-says.html
Saudi Arabia ’s  Power and Water
Utility Company for Jubail and Yanbu , known as Marafiq, signed
contracts for two projects in Jubail that include a reverse
osmosis desalination plant,  Asharq al-Awsat  said today.  The contracts also involve building 249 residential units
for Marafiq employees in Jabail, the newspaper said. It said the
RO desalination plant will produce 100,000 cubic meters of water
a day and be the fourth in the industrial city.  The contract for the water project was with Saudi Binladin
Group and  Acciona SA (ANA) ’s Acciona Agua unit, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donna Abu-Nasr in Beirut at 
 dabunasr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
